<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05039k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05039k">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05039k"> 39(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Hugh Price Hughes </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Hugh Price Hughes was a Welsh Protestant clergyman and religious reformer in the Methodist tradition. He served in multiple leadership roles in the Wesleyan Methodist Church and founded the <cite>Methodist Times</cite>. G.W. Foote (in a pamphlet) wrote a critique of Hughes claiming that a cobbler, &lsquo;wellknown in secular circles,&rsquo; had reconverted to Christianity before he died at the age of twenty-eight: <cite>The atheist shoemaker and the Rev. Hugh Price Hughes: or a study in lying with a full and complete exposure</cite> (London: R. Forder, 28 Stonecutter Street, E.C., 1894). </mm> </dd></dl>
